2.4.25  3:40 am   Many would say "Art imitates life", and some would even say "Life imitates art". Many also say "Imitation is the highest form of flattery"... so does this mean art is very fond of life? Or life is very fond of art? Both? Is this a chicken and egg situation? You can't really have art if you don't have life, but I would argue you can't have life without art. A life without art is barely life at all. So which imitated which first? Did they each imitate each other in tandem? Maybe life and art are even one in the same. Maybe everything is art. Maybe everything is life. Maybe... everything is... stuff. Woah.
